<h4>Acceptance</h4>
<p>These Terms of Use refer only to the BFI Screenonline site located at www.BFI Screenonline.co.uk (&quot;the Site&quot;) and not to any other websites operated or hosted by the British Film Institute (&quot;the bfi&quot;)</p>
<p>By using the Site you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use. We reserve the right to amend these Terms of Use from time to time without notice to you and you agree to be bound by any such changes in your subsequent use of the Site.</p>
<p>The agreement between you and the bfi formed on the basis of these Terms of Use (the &quot;Agreement&quot;) shall terminate immediately if you breach these Terms of Use.  The bfi reserves the right to terminate this Agreement at any time.  The termination of this Agreement or your right to use the Site is without prejudice to any rights which the bfi may have against you in respect of such breach.</p>


<h4>Intellectual Property Rights</h4>
<p>All materials available on the Site (the &quot;Materials&quot;) - including but not limited to text, video clips, audio clips, designs, logos, illustrations and still images - are protected by copyright, trademark and other intellectual property and proprietary rights and must not be used for any purpose other than educational, non-commercial viewing purposes, unless otherwise stated in pop-up notices throughout the Site.</p>
<p>The Materials contained in the Site are either owned by the bfi or have been licensed by the owners to the bfi for inclusion within the Site.  Under no circumstances may the Materials contained in the Site be copied, downloaded, reproduced, transmitted, broadcast, distributed or modified in any way, unless otherwise stated in pop-up notices throughout the Site.</p>
<p>The bfi would like to hear from any intellectual property rights owners who are not properly identified on the Site so that we may make the necessary corrections and display the appropriate notices.</p>
<p>ANY UNAUTHORISED USE OF MATERIAL ON THIS SITE MAY RESULT IN CIVIL AND CRIMINAL LIABILITY.</p>


